results.name: Decimal expansion of the integral_{x=0..Infinity} 1/x^x dx.
comment: "The function x^x grows even more quickly than Gamma(x) and the integral {0-inf} 1/x^x dx = 1.9954559575... and the integral {1-inf} 1/x^x dx = 0.7041699604... ." [Finch]
reference: Steven R. Finch, Mathematical Constants, Encyclopedia of Mathematics and its Applications, vol. 94, Cambridge University Press, p. 263.
mathematica: RealDigits[ NIntegrate[ 1/x^x, {x, 0, 100}, MaxRecursion -> 5000, MaxPoints -> 5000, AccuracyGoal-> 111, PrecisionGoal -> 111, WorkingPrecision -> 120], 10, 111][[1]]
